<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.AFRICA'S TRANSNET SETTLES WAGES WITH SOME STAFF.</title>
<headline>S.AFRICA'S TRANSNET SETTLES WAGES WITH SOME STAFF.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-08-12</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's state-owned transport corporation Transnet Ltd agreed to a 7.5 percent wage hike for about 35,000 workers in five unions on Tuesday, but would continue talks with the two major black unions, a spokeswoman said.</p>
<p>The Transnet spokeswoman said the settlement would add 7.5 percent to the wage bill, but declined to provide details of the terms agreed for different categories.</p>
<p>&quot;Talks with the remaining two unions are continuing,&quot; she said.</p>
<p>The spokeswoman said the continuing talks affected almost 50,000 of Transnet's 82,000 unionised staff. The corporation employs a total of 109,000 people.</p>
